<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
    <h1>Ember-x-editable-addon</h1>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3">
    Ember-x-editable-addon is an "x-editable like" Ember addon. It doesn not wrap the actual x-editable library,
    but was inspired by it. It provides much less functionality than the full x-editable. This was created because
    x-editable did not play nicely with Ember.
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
    <h2>Demo</h2>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3">
    <h2>Text</h2>
    {{ember-x-editable
    cancelAction='cancelAction'
    fontFamilyConfig=fontFamilyConfig
    isFieldEditing=isFieldEditing
    saveAction='saveAction'
    type='text'
    validator=textValidator
    value=textValue
    }}
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3">
    <h2>Select</h2>
    {{ember-x-editable
    cancelAction='cancelAction'
    changeAction='changeAction'
    content=selectContent
    fontFamilyConfig=fontFamilyConfig
    isFieldEditing=isFieldEditing
    saveAction='saveAction'
    type='select'
    validator=selectValidator
    value=selectValue
    }}
  </div>
</div>
